{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Silcoon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=265|prev=Wurmple|nextnum=267|next=Beautifly|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Silcoon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Silcoon\n|jname=カラサリス\n|jtranslit=Karasarisu\n|tmname=Karasalis\n|ndex=266\n|hdex=015\n|sdex=049\n|fbrow=155\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Bug\n|category=Cocoon\n|height-ftin=2\'00"\n|height-m=0.6\n|weight-lbs=22.0\n|weight-kg=10.0\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Shed Skin\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|expyield=72\n|g4exp=72\n|oldexp=71|\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=White\n|catchrate=120\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=silcoon\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Silcoon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'カラサリス\'\'\' \'\'Karasalis\'\') is a {{type|Bug}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Wurmple}} depending on its [[personality value]], starting at [[level]] 7, and it evolves into {{p|Beautifly}} starting at level 10.\n\n==Biology==\nSilcoon is a cocoon-like Pokémon that uses silk to attach itself to tree branches. It is almost completely covered in white silk with only two small holes. A pair of red eyes can be seen through the holes, but they are partially hidden by a rough fringe of silk. The silk forms a hard cocoon that it can use to repel enemy attacks. Dew and rainwater collect on the silk, which provides Silcoon with nourishment. Silcoon lives in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Forest Pokémon|forests}}, where it conserves energy by moving as little as possible.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:May Silcoon.png|thumb|left|220px|Silcoon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[May\'s Silcoon]]=====\nSilcoon debuted in \'\'[[AG024|A Corphish out of Water]]\'\', where {{an|May}}\'s Wurmple evolved into it alongside [[Jessie]]\'s own Wurmple, which evolved into a {{p|Cascoon}}. Both later evolved in \'\'[[AG028|Seeing is Believing]]\'\', with Silcoon evolving into Beautifly and Cascoon evolving into {{TP|Jessie|Dustox}}.\n\n====Minor appearances====\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG024|Silcoon|Ash\'s Pokédex|Silcoon, the Cocoon Pokémon. Silcoon is the evolved form of Wurmple. Using its thread to attach itself to a tree branch, it waits to evolve to its next stage. When it grows thirsty, it drinks the dew that collects on its string.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer===\nA Silcoon appeared in the [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer]], where it surrounded {{ga|May}} and her {{p|Torchic}}, only for Torchic to scare it away with a {{type|Fire}} attack.\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Silcoon Cascoon Adventures.png|thumb|250px|Silcoon in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Silcoon appeared in \'\'[[PS182|Making Mirth with Mightyena]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Mangadexheader}}\n{{Mangadexbody|Pokémon Adventures|[[PS182]]|The silk cocoon it spins winds it around tree branches to prevent it from falling and waits quietly inside for [[evolution]]. It peeps out through a small hole.{{tt|*|Chuang Yi\'s translation}}}}\n{{Mangadexbody|Pokémon Adventures|[[PS182]]|It tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits [[evolution]]. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.{{tt|*|VIZ Media}}}}\n{{Mangadexfooter}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Silcoon (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Bug}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=015|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep f